So at line 840, the test `Given an annotation with parameter` expects:
```kotlin
data class Foo
    @Bar1
    @Bar2("bar")
    @Bar3
    @Bar4
    constructor(private val foobar: Int) {
        fun foo(): String = "foo"
    }
```

With the fix, the class body should NOT be indented at 8 spaces. The correct formatting would be:
```kotlin
data class Foo
    @Bar1
    @Bar2("bar")
    @Bar3
    @Bar4
    constructor(private val foobar: Int) {
    fun foo(): String = "foo"
}
```

Note how the test at line 870 (`Given annotations without parameters`) already expects the correct behavior at lines 879-884:
```kotlin
data class Foo
    @Bar1 @Bar2
    constructor(private val foobar: Int) {
    fun foo(): String = "foo"
}
```

This confirms the fix is correct. The test at line 840 was incorrectly encoding the buggy behavior. Let me update it:

